cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper presents a computational model for the Hippocampus, a region of the brain responsible for episodic learning. As such, it is likely to fall under the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The model is also trained without external labels and uses local and immediate credit assignment, which suggests it may be relevant to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the model's performance on a classification benchmark, indicating relevance to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the model's alignment with current biological models suggests it may also be relevant to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
